WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:38.520
 Did you get the pastries, 
 Micheál? 

00:00:38.600 --> 00:00:41.480
 You didn't mention anything 
 about pastries. 

00:00:41.560 --> 00:00:44.080
 Yes, but we get them every morning. 

00:00:44.160 --> 00:00:49.280
 I might have remembered them had 
 you not got me up on my morning off.

00:00:49.360 --> 00:00:52.680
 It was you who wanted to work 
 different shifts! 

00:00:52.960 --> 00:00:56.560
 It seems we don't have them. 
 Sorry about that. 

00:00:56.960 --> 00:01:00.960
 So, that's 2 full Irish breakfasts 
 and 2 coffees? 

00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:05.840
 Mikey, did I switch off the cooker 
 this morning? 

00:01:05.920 --> 00:01:08.400
 This is a great time to remember it.

00:01:08.480 --> 00:01:10.680
 Don't start, I think I did but..! 

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:13.200
 You were in the kitchen 
 as I was leaving. 

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.440
 -Are you busy? 
 -No, you're fine. 

00:01:15.520 --> 00:01:18.720
 -Call the man downstairs. 
 -He doesn't have a key. 

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:21.640
 He'll see the smoke 
 if the house is on fire! 

00:01:21.720 --> 00:01:23.640
 Thanks for the reassurance! 

00:01:23.720 --> 00:01:25.880
 Mikey, the customers are waiting. 

00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:28.840
 I just wanted to check something 
 with Mikey. 

00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:31.040
 -Something on the menu? 
 -No. 

00:01:31.120 --> 00:01:35.440
 -So, you haven't ordered anything? 
 -No. I should go. 

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:38.600
 I'll see you later, Mikey. 

00:01:40.520 --> 00:01:42.920
 -Pauline! 
 -Hi, Daniel. 

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:45.480
 She shouldn't have treated you 
 like that. 

00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:47.560
 Who are you telling? 

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:50.520
 Don't pay any attention to her. 
 She's not all there. 

00:01:50.600 --> 00:01:54.200
 -Perhaps you're right. 
 -I'm glad I met you. Have a seat. 

00:01:54.280 --> 00:01:56.000
 Why? 

00:01:56.080 --> 00:01:58.880
 Will you be in Ros na Rún 
 all morning? 

00:01:58.960 --> 00:02:00.960
 Yes, as it happens. 

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:04.920
 I want to talk to you. 
 I'm embarrassed about the other day.

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:09.480
 Daniel, we all have our own problems.
 As you've just seen! 

00:02:09.560 --> 00:02:13.360
 I suppose so. I will be 
 in Tigh Thaidhg at about 1pm. 

00:02:13.440 --> 00:02:15.640
 You're on. 

00:02:16.600 --> 00:02:18.800
 You didn't say anything to her? 

00:02:18.880 --> 00:02:20.680
 Don't you believe me? 

00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:23.120
 Forgive me Berni if I don't! 

00:02:23.200 --> 00:02:27.320
 Myself and Pauline are finished 
 so stop tormenting her! 

00:02:27.400 --> 00:02:30.760
 Besides, it's no concern of yours! 

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:36.480
 Right so. Keys, wallet..! 

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:39.360
 Condoms! 

00:02:39.440 --> 00:02:42.160
 Mack, you are going to visit 
 your sister! 

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:46.440
 I know but you'd never know who 
 I'd meet between here and Belfast. 

00:02:46.520 --> 00:02:49.120
 -You wish! 
 -Mobile. 

00:02:49.640 --> 00:02:52.280
 -Did you see my mobile? 
 -No, I didn't. 

00:02:52.360 --> 00:02:54.360
 It must be upstairs. 

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:59.320
 That lad has such notions 
 about himself. 

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:02.200
 -Yes, but he's good fun. 
 -Yeah. 

00:03:02.280 --> 00:03:05.120
 It's weird having a lad in the house.

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:06.800
 How? 

00:03:07.040 --> 00:03:08.880
 I don't know. 

00:03:08.960 --> 00:03:12.760
 It's strange to find a lad 
 looking at himself in the mirror... 

00:03:12.840 --> 00:03:16.360
 ..when you come out of your bedroom. 
 It's a big change. 

00:03:16.440 --> 00:03:20.280
 Speaking of which! You need 
 to change some of your habits. 

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:22.360
 What do you mean? 

00:03:22.440 --> 00:03:25.320
 Your clothes are thrown 
 all over the house. 

00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:27.520
 I'm not that bad. 

00:03:27.600 --> 00:03:29.600
 No you're worse, Róise. 

00:03:30.920 --> 00:03:32.720
 -Dad! 
 -Hi. 

00:03:32.800 --> 00:03:35.800
 -Is everything alright here? 
 -Yes, fine. 

00:03:35.880 --> 00:03:38.080
 You'll soon need to put the heat on. 

00:03:38.160 --> 00:03:42.360
 There was an airlock in the radiator 
 in your bedroom, wasn't there? 

00:03:42.440 --> 00:03:45.240
 -Yes, there was. 
 -Mack can fix that. 

00:03:45.320 --> 00:03:48.360
 -He's very handy around the house. 
 -Is he really? 

00:03:48.440 --> 00:03:52.240
 -Yes, would you like a cup of coffee?
 -I'll have a quick one. 

00:03:52.320 --> 00:03:55.720
 Hey sex slaves. That threesome 
 last night was great... 

00:03:55.800 --> 00:03:59.200
 ..but you can't leave 
 this stuff on my bed. Vince! 

00:03:59.280 --> 00:04:01.960
 -Mack. 
 -That was a joke! 

00:04:04.360 --> 00:04:08.280
 I better go or I'll miss the train. 
 See you later. 

00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:16.200
 Would you like some toast? 

00:04:16.280 --> 00:04:18.680
 That would be great, thank you. 

00:04:20.760 --> 00:04:22.760
 Tell me this, Séamus. 

00:04:22.840 --> 00:04:26.840
 Did you get a bump on the head 
 recently? 

00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:30.160
 Me? No, why? 

00:04:30.840 --> 00:04:34.840
 This is the first time 
 you've offered to make me toast... 

00:04:34.920 --> 00:04:37.920
 ..since I came to live 
 in this house 7 years ago. 

00:04:38.040 --> 00:04:40.040
 That's why! 

00:04:40.120 --> 00:04:42.160
 Do you want it or not? 

00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:44.080
 Of course I want it. 

00:04:44.160 --> 00:04:46.600
 What's unusual is wonderful. 

00:04:53.240 --> 00:04:56.800
 For the love of God. 
 Are you trying to kill me? 

00:04:56.880 --> 00:04:59.520
 What did you spread on the toast? 

00:04:59.600 --> 00:05:01.520
 Butter, that's all. 

00:05:01.840 --> 00:05:05.000
 It's a strange tasting butter. 
 Where did you get it? 

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:12.400
 I'll put it this way, 
 I found it in the most unusual place!

00:05:13.760 --> 00:05:15.760
 Come in. 

00:05:16.320 --> 00:05:17.920
 Hello. 

00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:22.160
 Things turn up in 
 the strangest of places! 

00:05:22.240 --> 00:05:25.280
 -Mo told me what happened. 
 -What's that, Sarah? 

00:05:25.400 --> 00:05:29.880
 About the ancient butter herself 
 and Séamus found in the bog. 

00:05:29.960 --> 00:05:32.160
 What do you mean, ancient butter? 

00:05:32.240 --> 00:05:36.680
 Butter from the old days. She said 
 there was a large amount of it. 

00:05:36.760 --> 00:05:41.120
 That's what you spread on my toast! 
 You should be ashamed of yourself! 

00:05:41.200 --> 00:05:43.320
 What are you saying, Cóilín? 

00:05:43.400 --> 00:05:49.200
 He tried to kill me by putting 
 that butter on my toast, the idiot! 

00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:51.600
 That's what I'm telling you. 

00:05:51.680 --> 00:05:57.000
 It didn't kill you. 
 A bit of butter never harmed anyone.

00:05:57.080 --> 00:06:00.440
 Why didn't you have some 
 if that's the case? 

00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:03.600
 Stop, in the name of God. 
 This is big news! 

00:06:06.280 --> 00:06:08.280
 Just these two, Peadar. 

00:06:08.360 --> 00:06:12.440
 The Auto Trader. Are you thinking 
 of adding to your fleet? 

00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:14.520
 You wouldn't know. 

00:06:17.600 --> 00:06:19.600
 Hello? Oh, hello. 

00:06:20.080 --> 00:06:22.080
 I'm on my way now. 

00:06:22.480 --> 00:06:27.120
 I'll be in Heuston at about 2pm and 
 then I'll go straight to Connolly. 

00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:30.280
 I'll be in Belfast at about 5.30pm. 
 Yeah okay, bye. 

00:06:30.760 --> 00:06:32.760
 You have a long journey ahead of you.

00:06:32.840 --> 00:06:34.880
 I can take it easy on the train. 

00:06:34.960 --> 00:06:36.960
 Why don't you take the car? 

00:06:37.040 --> 00:06:41.040
 I'll leave the car here 
 to make me money while I'm away. 

00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:45.120
 Listen to the businessman, 
 taking it easy on the train... 

00:06:45.200 --> 00:06:49.400
 ..while some poor idiot earns him 
 money driving the hackney. 

00:06:49.480 --> 00:06:54.040
 -I was that idiot for long enough.Bye
 -Bye. Safe home. 

00:06:58.280 --> 00:07:00.640
 There could be a very important dig. 

00:07:01.120 --> 00:07:03.440
 What are you talking about? 

00:07:03.520 --> 00:07:05.520
 If they find something valuable... 

00:07:05.600 --> 00:07:09.080
 ..the place would be full 
 of archaeologists. 

00:07:09.160 --> 00:07:13.520
 -They could be here for years. 
 -It would be good for the area. 

00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:15.680
 Do you know exactly what will happen?

00:07:15.760 --> 00:07:18.800
 Nobody will be able to gather 
 turf next year. 

00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:21.080
 I'll solve that problem. 

00:07:21.160 --> 00:07:25.560
 I'll put it back where I found it 
 and that's that! 

00:07:25.640 --> 00:07:30.240
 No, you won't! It's against the law 
 not to inform the museum. 

00:07:30.320 --> 00:07:35.000
 The museum won't be any the wiser if
 certain people keep their mouths shut

00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:39.560
 Really? Who was with you 
 when you found the butter? 

00:07:39.640 --> 00:07:42.000
 The sergeant's daughter. 

00:07:42.080 --> 00:07:44.920
 Sarah is right. You have no choice, 
 Séamus. 

00:07:46.040 --> 00:07:49.800
 Mo is no informer. She won't say 
 anything. I'm sure of it. 

00:07:49.880 --> 00:07:52.320
 If she doesn't, I will. 

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:57.160
 I won't keep quiet. It's 
 our duty to inform the authorities. 

00:07:57.880 --> 00:08:00.520
 This had nothing to do with you. 

00:08:00.600 --> 00:08:04.200
 But you had to stick 
 your big nose into it! 

00:08:04.280 --> 00:08:08.560
 Sarah is right, 
 you must fulfil your obligations. 

00:08:13.240 --> 00:08:15.440
 -I'll have another one. 
 -Another? 

00:08:15.520 --> 00:08:17.280
 Is that alright? 

00:08:17.360 --> 00:08:19.520
 You're knocking them back, 
 that's all. 

00:08:19.600 --> 00:08:22.000
 All the better for you. 

00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:25.480
 It's the same old story 
 for lone parents. 

00:08:25.560 --> 00:08:29.600
 Children have such problems 
 accepting someone new in your life. 

00:08:29.680 --> 00:08:31.680
 I can cope with that. 

00:08:31.760 --> 00:08:35.760
 But abuse from the ex-wife 
 of a man whom I'm no longer seeing. 

00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:39.440
 There are people like that. 
 They're jealousy-ridden. 

00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:42.920
 -I don't like to be mean but..! 
 -Berni's like that? 

00:08:43.000 --> 00:08:47.800
 Yes. Perhaps Micheál wasn't ready 
 for a relationship but..! 

00:08:49.560 --> 00:08:53.280
 She took it as a personal insult 
 that he had a new woman. 

00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:55.160
 I think so. 

00:08:55.240 --> 00:08:59.200
 Nancy used to torment herself 
 about that too. 

00:08:59.280 --> 00:09:04.000
 She was always questioning me 
 about people I met through work. 

00:09:04.080 --> 00:09:08.240
 Maybe she was just interested 
 in your life? 

00:09:08.320 --> 00:09:11.800
 She was much more obsessive 
 than that. 

00:09:12.040 --> 00:09:14.440
 She used to call me all the time... 

00:09:14.520 --> 00:09:17.520
 ...wanting to know where I was, 
 who I was with. 

00:09:17.600 --> 00:09:21.560
 If I switched off the phone 
 for a meeting she'd be enraged. 

00:09:21.640 --> 00:09:24.400
 -That's terrible. 
 -Yes. 

00:09:25.640 --> 00:09:30.160
 I don't know how I didn't realise it 
 before we got married. 

00:09:30.240 --> 00:09:32.640
 We were very close at the start. 

00:09:33.800 --> 00:09:37.200
 Listen to me talking nonsense 
 again. I'm sorry. 

00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:40.720
 Don't be. You have to confide 
 in someone. 

00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:50.800
 Do you want something? 

00:09:50.880 --> 00:09:52.880
 I was looking for you. 

00:09:52.960 --> 00:09:55.040
 Three and four there. 

00:09:55.120 --> 00:09:57.120
 This is a game to be played alone. 

00:09:57.200 --> 00:10:01.400
 You'll be alone at your party too 
 if we don't get a move on. 

00:10:01.480 --> 00:10:03.480
 And so what if I am? 

00:10:03.560 --> 00:10:06.600
 Look, there is a lot of work 
 involved. 

00:10:06.680 --> 00:10:09.320
 I thought our plan would work. 

00:10:09.400 --> 00:10:11.720
 How will it benefit us? 

00:10:11.800 --> 00:10:16.080
 Bringing the village's scroungers 
 and spongers in. 

00:10:16.160 --> 00:10:20.880
 Having them there all night long 
 singing and looking for free beer. 

00:10:21.160 --> 00:10:25.080
 I thought you were happy to go ahead 
 with this a few days ago? 

00:10:25.160 --> 00:10:28.400
 Not anymore. So forget it. 
 We needn't bother with it. 

00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:21.840
 And E1.20. Thanks. 

00:11:21.920 --> 00:11:24.120
 Is it a 21st? 

00:11:24.200 --> 00:11:26.080
 No. This person is 50. 

00:11:26.160 --> 00:11:30.280
 All we need is finger food. 
 Chicken goujons, paté and crackers. 

00:11:30.360 --> 00:11:33.520
 -You know yourself. 
 -Will it be held this weekend? 

00:11:33.600 --> 00:11:38.040
 That's the problem. 
 It's tomorrow night. I'm in a fix. 

00:11:38.120 --> 00:11:40.600
 Tomorrow night? 

00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:43.880
 I know but I'd be very grateful. 
 I'd pay you well. 

00:11:43.960 --> 00:11:48.160
 We know but we're very busy 
 what with Jack gone and everything. 

00:11:48.280 --> 00:11:50.240
 There wouldn't be that much involved.

00:11:50.320 --> 00:11:53.640
 -I suppose not. 
 -I'm sorry Angela..! 

00:11:53.720 --> 00:11:57.360
 Excuse me Micheál but Berni and I 
 can sort this out ourselves. 

00:11:57.480 --> 00:11:59.880
 -I'll do it. 
 -But Berni..! 

00:11:59.960 --> 00:12:04.360
 Micheál, relax! 
 I'll be doing all the work, not you! 

00:12:05.560 --> 00:12:08.480
 What type of budget did you 
 have in mind? 

00:12:08.560 --> 00:12:11.920
 You make out a list 
 and we can come to some arrangement. 

00:12:39.040 --> 00:12:43.840
 We'll be coming to you 
 half an hour into the programme. 

00:12:44.560 --> 00:12:47.200
 Great, goodbye Mairéad. 

00:12:47.920 --> 00:12:51.000
 Is this a radio station 
 or a train station? 

00:12:51.080 --> 00:12:52.880
 I'm sorry Caitríona. 

00:12:52.960 --> 00:12:57.920
 The lock is broken in my car 
 and I was afraid to leave them in it.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:01.080
 And I'm homeless at the moment 
 as well. 

00:13:01.160 --> 00:13:02.560
 Why? 

00:13:02.640 --> 00:13:04.840
 Because of my landlord. 

00:13:04.920 --> 00:13:07.360
 He said he's selling the house. 

00:13:07.440 --> 00:13:09.240
 Is he? 

00:13:09.320 --> 00:13:12.120
 I think it has more to do 
 with the fact... 

00:13:12.200 --> 00:13:15.000
 ..that I refused to pay E300 extra 
 a month. 

00:13:15.080 --> 00:13:16.880
 That's terrible. 

00:13:16.960 --> 00:13:21.080
 Yes, so here I am with my house on my
 back. 

00:13:21.160 --> 00:13:23.160
 Poor Rory! 

00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:30.440
 Honestly Dad, I don't know what you 
 saw in her in the first place. 

00:13:30.520 --> 00:13:32.520
 She had no style. 

00:13:32.600 --> 00:13:35.320
 20/20 vision is a wonderful thing! 

00:13:35.400 --> 00:13:39.400
 Even so. It would do you good 
 to get rid of this stuff. 

00:13:39.480 --> 00:13:42.720
 It's bad feng shui 
 to have it lying around. 

00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:45.840
 Don't tell me you believe 
 in that claptrap? 

00:13:45.920 --> 00:13:50.080
 No, I don't. 
 Janet believes in it, though. 

00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:52.160
 Wherever she is. 

00:13:52.240 --> 00:13:55.040
 You haven't been able 
 to contact her? 

00:13:55.120 --> 00:13:57.120
 No, incredibly I haven't. 

00:13:58.040 --> 00:14:00.400
 Do you think she is avoiding you? 

00:14:00.480 --> 00:14:02.680
 I don't think she is. I know she is. 

00:14:02.760 --> 00:14:06.000
 I hoped that she would answer 
 your calls. 

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:11.040
 I don't know why you hope. 
 She does it to me all the time. 

00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:13.120
 Are you alright? 

00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:15.200
 Yeah, I am. 

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:18.200
 Sometimes I get a bit dizzy. 

00:14:18.440 --> 00:14:21.040
 You should lie down for a while, Dad.

00:14:21.800 --> 00:14:24.320
 Maybe I will. For an hour or so. 

00:14:25.160 --> 00:14:26.720
 You're alright. 

00:14:44.120 --> 00:14:46.640
 Janet, this is Suzy, your sister! 

00:14:46.720 --> 00:14:50.320
 I'm fed up of calling you 
 and not getting a reply. 

00:14:50.400 --> 00:14:54.400
 Call me, now! I'm in Dad's apartment 
 in Ros na Rún. It's urgent. 

00:14:54.480 --> 00:14:57.200
 In case you've forgotten the number 
 is 091..! 

00:14:57.960 --> 00:14:59.960
 So, I don't love you? 

00:15:00.920 --> 00:15:02.440
 No. 

00:15:02.520 --> 00:15:05.440
 Evan, what have I done wrong? 

00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:12.680
 Is that the reason Micheál has been 
 scratched out of this picture? 

00:15:12.760 --> 00:15:14.760
 Yes. 

00:15:14.840 --> 00:15:17.520
 But Evan that's a terrible thing 
 to do. 

00:15:19.720 --> 00:15:21.760
 Listen to me now. 

00:15:22.960 --> 00:15:26.960
 -Who told you that I didn't love you?
 -Mammy. 

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:28.760
 Mammy? 

00:15:28.840 --> 00:15:32.400
 So Mammy told you that 
 I didn't love you? 

00:15:34.960 --> 00:15:36.760
 Berni, come here. 

00:15:36.840 --> 00:15:39.640
 -I'm busy. 
 -What have you been telling Evan? 

00:15:39.720 --> 00:15:41.720
 Shh, the customers might hear you. 

00:15:41.800 --> 00:15:45.720
 -Did you tell him I didn't love him? 
 -Now is not the time. 

00:15:45.800 --> 00:15:49.400
 Perhaps not. I'll be back at 5 pm 
 when it's quiet... 

00:15:49.480 --> 00:15:51.720
 ..to discuss this. Do you understand?

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:54.240
 Alright! Alright! 

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:41.680
 I like the idea! 

00:18:42.400 --> 00:18:46.360
 You haven't said much, Caitríona. 
 Are you happy with it? 

00:18:46.440 --> 00:18:50.640
 It's not that I'm against 
 hosting a programme with Rory..! 

00:18:50.720 --> 00:18:53.480
 -I should hope not. 
 -You know well I'm not. 

00:18:53.560 --> 00:18:55.560
 -But..! 
 -But what? 

00:18:56.680 --> 00:19:01.160
 I don't think it's very practical 
 in a small station like this. 

00:19:01.240 --> 00:19:05.360
 We barely have enough people 
 to put out the current schedule. 

00:19:05.440 --> 00:19:08.200
 Not to mention doubling up like this.

00:19:08.280 --> 00:19:11.640
 Well, we need a central focus 
 within the schedule. 

00:19:11.720 --> 00:19:14.560
 I think the two of you together 
 can do that. 

00:19:15.120 --> 00:19:18.440
 -It's worth a try. 
 -Sure. 

00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:21.080
 That's that then. 

00:19:21.160 --> 00:19:23.160
 I need to make a move. 

00:19:23.240 --> 00:19:25.720
 I'll speak to you both tomorrow. 

00:19:28.320 --> 00:19:31.720
 Mickey, we'll be closing 
 as soon as they leave. 

00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:34.560
 I've just made a fresh pot of coffee.

00:19:34.640 --> 00:19:36.800
 -It doesn't matter. 
 -Are you serious? 

00:19:36.880 --> 00:19:41.480
 Do I look like I'm joking? Throw out 
 that coffee and clean the machine. 

00:19:41.560 --> 00:19:43.720
 You're the boss. 

00:19:57.800 --> 00:20:00.040
 Janet. This is Suzy. 

00:20:01.440 --> 00:20:03.720
 Did you not get my messages? 

00:20:04.720 --> 00:20:06.720
 That's very strange. 

00:20:07.080 --> 00:20:11.800
 You haven't paid your family 
 much attention recently, have you? 

00:20:11.880 --> 00:20:14.600
 You know well what I mean by that. 

00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:17.720
 Dad says you haven't called him 
 in 6 months. 

00:20:17.800 --> 00:20:20.520
 Don't you know how sick he was? 

00:20:22.400 --> 00:20:25.320
 You visited him while he was 
 in a coma. 

00:20:25.400 --> 00:20:28.560
 Where are you now? He is on dialysis.

00:20:29.680 --> 00:20:31.680
 Yes, dialysis. 

00:20:31.760 --> 00:20:34.960
 His kidneys are badly damaged. 
 He nearly died. 

00:20:36.560 --> 00:20:39.480
 No, he's not here now. 
 He's at work. 

00:20:39.560 --> 00:20:42.120
 He's not looking after himself 
 at all. 

00:20:42.200 --> 00:20:45.720
 But you're obviously 
 not very concerned. 

00:20:45.800 --> 00:20:50.640
 He's just arrived. I don't want 
 to upset him. Just call him okay? 

00:20:50.720 --> 00:20:52.520
 Bye. 

00:20:55.200 --> 00:20:57.000
 -Hi. 
 -Hi love. 

00:20:57.080 --> 00:20:59.080
 Who were you talking to? 

00:20:59.160 --> 00:21:01.360
 -Janet! 
 -Janet? 

00:21:01.440 --> 00:21:03.520
 -Did she call? 
 -No. 

00:21:04.600 --> 00:21:06.520
 I called her. 

00:21:06.600 --> 00:21:10.320
 But she said she'd be 
 in contact soon. 

00:21:10.400 --> 00:21:12.200
 How soon? 

00:21:12.280 --> 00:21:14.280
 You know Janet. 

00:21:14.800 --> 00:21:17.400
 The party is sorted now. 

00:21:17.480 --> 00:21:20.120
 Berni is preparing the food. 

00:21:20.200 --> 00:21:23.880
 We're okay if the woman from Aran 
 is helping us! 

00:21:23.960 --> 00:21:27.520
 I won't be under pressure. 
 I can enjoy the occasion. 

00:21:27.600 --> 00:21:31.800
 I thought I was supposed 
 to be the one to enjoy myself. 

00:21:34.280 --> 00:21:36.720
 Hi Angela, how are things? 

00:21:36.800 --> 00:21:39.160
 I don't know why I bother sometimes. 

00:21:39.240 --> 00:21:41.040
 What do you mean? 

00:21:41.120 --> 00:21:44.920
 -Tadhg has no interest in this party.
 -Doesn't he? 

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:48.120
 -He is being childish. 
 -That's men for you. 

00:21:48.200 --> 00:21:50.200
 My man anyway. 

00:21:50.280 --> 00:21:53.440
 I could have a word with him 
 if you like? 

00:21:53.520 --> 00:21:56.600
 He might listen to someone 
 other than me. 

00:21:56.680 --> 00:22:00.680
 It's worth a try. I'd say he just 
 needs a bit of flattery. 

00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:06.280
 Hi Tadhg. 

00:22:08.800 --> 00:22:11.000
 Suzy, it's you. 

00:22:12.000 --> 00:22:14.600
 Berni, just the woman 
 I was looking for. 

00:22:14.680 --> 00:22:16.280
 Why? 

00:22:16.360 --> 00:22:19.080
 Did you have any ideas 
 about the food? 

00:22:19.160 --> 00:22:23.840
 Yes, a few. To tell you the truth, 
 I came in for a drink. 

00:22:23.920 --> 00:22:26.360
 I need it after the day I've had. 

00:22:26.440 --> 00:22:29.440
 Of course. What will you have? 
 It's on the house. 

00:22:29.520 --> 00:22:32.040
 -I'll have a G&amp;T then, please. 
 -Right. 

00:22:41.200 --> 00:22:43.800
 Berni! Berni! 

00:22:54.480 --> 00:22:56.480
 Sorry, we're closed. 

00:22:57.000 --> 00:22:58.800
 I'm sorry. 

00:23:02.240 --> 00:23:05.320
 Don't worry Tadhg. 
 It'll be a great night! 

00:23:05.400 --> 00:23:07.400
 Do you think so? 

00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:10.560
 Yes. If I say it'll be a good night,
 it will be. 

00:23:10.640 --> 00:23:12.840
 You seem very sure. 

00:23:12.920 --> 00:23:16.160
 I always keep my word, 
 you'll see. 

00:23:17.240 --> 00:23:19.640
 That could be very interesting. 

00:23:20.560 --> 00:23:22.880
 Did he tell you about the butter? 

00:23:22.960 --> 00:23:26.200
 No. Don't tell me 
 you're making butter, Séamus. 

00:23:26.280 --> 00:23:30.520
 For the love of God, you can't even 
 relax in the pub now. 

00:23:30.600 --> 00:23:33.600
 Relax? And such an historic story 
 on our doorstep. 

00:23:33.680 --> 00:23:35.680
 What's this, Séamus? 

00:23:35.800 --> 00:23:39.600
 Hello, Cóilín. Here's the man 
 who'll tell us all about it. 

00:23:39.680 --> 00:23:43.760
 -Were you talking to the museum? 
 -What friggin' museum? 

00:23:43.840 --> 00:23:47.040
 -The museum. 
 -What did they think of your news? 

00:23:47.120 --> 00:23:52.720
 The girl in the office told me that 
 their archaeologist is in Co. Clare. 

00:23:52.800 --> 00:23:56.000
 She said that she would try 
 to contact him. 

00:23:56.080 --> 00:23:58.080
 I wonder which archaeologist it is? 

00:23:58.160 --> 00:24:00.760
 As if you know any of them! 

00:24:00.840 --> 00:24:03.120
 I think she said Dr. de Brún. 

00:24:03.280 --> 00:24:05.360
 Dr. Alasdar de Brún? 

00:24:05.440 --> 00:24:07.640
 I'm not sure. 

00:24:07.720 --> 00:24:10.800
 I bet it's him. He is a lovely man. 

00:24:10.920 --> 00:24:14.120
 He used to come here years ago 
 to learn Irish. 

00:24:14.200 --> 00:24:16.200
 He got an earful from you! 

00:24:16.280 --> 00:24:19.560
 You probably couldn't keep 
 your mouth shut then either. 

00:24:19.680 --> 00:24:23.480
 What is there for him 
 around here anyway? 

00:24:23.560 --> 00:24:26.160
 An important discovery 
 of ancient butter. 

00:24:26.240 --> 00:24:29.840
 Séamus and the sergeant's daughter 
 found it in the bog. 

00:24:29.920 --> 00:24:32.920
 Something like that was found 
 back home years ago. 

00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:36.000
 -There was a lot of talk about it. 
 -See, Séamus? 

00:24:36.080 --> 00:24:40.480
 Next you'll be giving guided tours 
 of Ros na Rún's history! 

00:24:40.560 --> 00:24:43.560
 As if I don't have enough 
 on my plate! 

00:24:43.640 --> 00:24:47.440
 -Berni, I'd like a word with you. 
 -Go on! 

00:24:47.520 --> 00:24:49.840
 Privately, please. 

00:24:50.440 --> 00:24:52.840
 Right then, excuse me. 

00:24:58.480 --> 00:25:00.040
 Angela! 

00:25:00.120 --> 00:25:03.520
 It's sorted. He's looking forward 
 to the party. 

00:25:03.600 --> 00:25:05.880
 You're joking! 

00:25:05.960 --> 00:25:08.000
 -He's fine with it. 
 -Well done. 

00:25:08.080 --> 00:25:10.920
 I'll call in tomorrow 
 to discuss everything. 

00:25:11.000 --> 00:25:13.560
 Right, well done. 

00:25:14.320 --> 00:25:17.200
 It's one thing to say it to me. 
 I'm an adult. 

00:25:17.280 --> 00:25:21.240
 It's an entirely different matter 
 to say it to a child. 

00:25:21.320 --> 00:25:24.120
 Are you telling me how 
 to raise my child? 

00:25:24.200 --> 00:25:28.040
 No, I'm not. I'm not telling you now
 and I never will again. 

00:25:29.160 --> 00:25:31.400
 So, what are you trying to tell me? 

00:25:32.760 --> 00:25:37.400
 I've decided not to have anything 
 to do with Evan in the future. 

00:25:38.120 --> 00:25:40.240
 -Micheál! 
 -End of story. 

00:25:40.320 --> 00:25:45.680
 You're willing to lie to a little 
 boy and tell him I don't love him. 

00:25:45.760 --> 00:25:49.360
 After all I've done for him, 
 for both of you. 

00:25:49.440 --> 00:25:52.320
 I can't put up with that. 

00:25:52.400 --> 00:25:54.400
 It wasn't like that. 

00:25:54.480 --> 00:25:58.320
 This is how it is and that's how 
 it's going to be. That's that. 

00:25:58.400 --> 00:26:01.240
 Don't you realise 
 this is breaking my heart? 

00:26:01.320 --> 00:26:03.280
 But you leave me with no alternative.

00:26:03.360 --> 00:26:07.040
 I pity him. I pity him 
 having you as a mother. 

00:26:07.120 --> 00:26:10.120
 Your maliciousness 
 will hurt him the most. 

